The Bank of Japan bought a modest amountof dollars this morning, possibly around 200 to 300 mln,dealers said.    One dealer said the central bank bought about 200 mln dlrsthrough brokers and the rest through banks. The buying beganwhen the dollar was at about 149.60 yen, and helped drive theU.S. Currency up to around 150, he said.    Another said the central bank seemed to be trying to pushthe dollar up above 150 yen. But heavy selling at around thatlevel quickly pushed the dollar back down towards 149 yen,dealers said. REUTER&#3;